from IPython.display import Audio, display
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import torch
import wavenet_features as wf

The dataset¶

  • 1024 examples
  • Each example is 4 seconds long
  • Sums of pairs of sinusoids with random phases and frequencies chosen from $\{220.0,\, 391.2,\, 695.7,\, 1237.2,\, 2200.0\}$ (geometric sequence)
In [2]:
sample_rate = 16000

examples = wf.make_dataset(
    n_examples=12,
    duration_secs=4,
    sample_rate=sample_rate,
    freqs=wf.get_frequencies(220, 2200, 5),
    n_sines_per_example=2)

def configure_time_axis(ax):
    xticks = ax.get_xticks()
    ax.set_xticks(xticks, xticks / sample_rate * 1e3)
    ax.set_xlabel('Time (ms)')
    
ms2samples = lambda n_ms : round(n_ms * 1e-3 * sample_rate)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 4, figsize=(12, 6))

for ax, example in zip(axes.flatten(), examples):
    ax.plot(example[:ms2samples(10)])
    configure_time_axis(ax)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

for example in examples:
    display(Audio(example, rate=sample_rate))

Generated examples seeded from the validation dataset¶

In [3]:
gen_duration_secs = 0.01
model = torch.load('snapshots/dataset1_2022-08-24_06-02-38')
model.cpu()

generated_examples = []

np.random.seed(0)
for _ in range(5):
    prefix = wf.make_dataset(
        n_examples=1,
        duration_secs=model.receptive_field / sample_rate,
        sample_rate=sample_rate,
        freqs=wf.get_frequencies(220, 2200, 5),
        n_sines_per_example=2)[0]
    model.eval()
    generated = wf.generate_example(model, prefix, n_samples=round(gen_duration_secs * sample_rate))
    generated_examples.append(generated)

In [4]:
def preview_generated_examples(generated_examples):
    subplot_aspect = 3 / 20
    subplot_width = 8
    subplot_height = subplot_aspect * subplot_width
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(
        len(generated_examples),
        figsize=(subplot_width, len(generated_examples) * subplot_height))
    
    for ax, generated in zip(axes, generated_examples):
        preview_size_ms = 10
        preview_size_samples = ms2samples(preview_size_ms)
        ax.axvline(preview_size_samples // 2, alpha=0.5, color='red', linestyle='--')
        ax.plot(generated[len(prefix) - preview_size_samples // 2:len(prefix) + preview_size_samples // 2])
        configure_time_axis(ax)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

preview_generated_examples(generated_examples)

Generated examples seeded from individual sinusoids¶

In [5]:
prefix_freqs = wf.get_frequencies(220, 2200, 5)
generated_examples = []

for prefix_freq in prefix_freqs:
    ts = np.arange(model.receptive_field) / sample_rate
    prefix = np.sin(2 * np.pi * prefix_freq * ts)
    model.eval()
    generated = wf.generate_example(model, prefix, n_samples=round(gen_duration_secs * sample_rate))
    generated_examples.append(generated)
